[38;2;142;68;207m[1m  ━━ novaflow.ai SYNTHESIS ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━[0m

    BRCA1 is the archetypal genome-caretaker tumor suppressor. The 1,863-aa nuclear phosphoprotein (P38398) anchors the BRCA1-Associated genome Surveillance Complex (BASC), coordinating ATM/ATR-driven damage sensing, RAD51-mediated homologous recombination (HR), and cell-cycle checkpoint enforcement at G1/S and G2/M. Its RING domain confers E3 ubiquitin ligase activity that builds atypical Lys6-linked polyubiquitin chains on substrates including CtIP and γH2AX-flanking chromatin, while the tandem BRCT domains read phospho-Ser motifs on partners like Abraxas, BACH1/FANCJ, and CtIP — the three mutually exclusive BRCT complexes (A, B, C) that route DSBs toward end resection and HR rather than error-prone NHEJ.
    Biologically, BRCA1 loss collapses high-fidelity DSB repair, forcing cells onto mutagenic alternative end-joining and replication-stress pathways. The resulting genomic instability — chromosomal rearrangements, large indels, and the characteristic HRD mutational signatures (COSMIC SBS3, ID6, and large-scale state transitions) — is the mechanistic basis for the breast, ovarian, fallopian-tube, pancreatic, and prostate cancer spectrum seen in germline carriers. Penetrance is high: ~65–75% lifetime breast cancer risk and ~40% ovarian risk for pathogenic variant carriers, with a strong bias toward basal-like, triple-negative histology.
    Clinically, BRCA1 status is directly actionable. HR-deficient tumors are synthetic-lethal with PARP inhibitors (olaparib, talazoparib, niraparib, rucaparib), all FDA-approved across BRCA-mutant breast, ovarian, pancreatic, and prostate indications, and are hypersensitive to platinum chemotherapy and topoisomerase I poisons. Resistance arises predictably through BRCA1 reversion mutations, 53BP1/REV7/Shieldin loss restoring resection, or replication-fork protection rescue — all monitorable by ctDNA. Variant interpretation hinges on ClinVar/ENIGMA curation plus functional assays (saturation genome editing of the BRCT and RING domains has now classified the majority of missense VUS).
    Experimentally, the 22-exon, ~110 kb locus and 47 annotated transcripts demand careful isoform handling: BRCA1-Δ11q lacks the central exon 11 and partially rescues PARPi sensitivity, so RNA-seq quantification at the isoform level (not gene level) is essential when phenotyping. For functional work, RAD51 foci formation after ionizing radiation remains the gold-standard HR readout; complement with DR-GFP reporters, RPA/BrdU resection assays, and PARPi/cisplatin dose-response. CRISPR knock-in of specific VUS into HCC1937 or RPE1 backgrounds, paired with isogenic BRCA1-proficient controls, is the cleanest design for separating loss-of-function from hypomorphic alleles.

